32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
246 704 1669 (The Global Information Infrastructure \(GII\) is seen as a means to economic growth,) 1669 SB
246 763 1756 (competitiveness and socio-cultural development. The precise requirements for the global) 1756 SB
246 822 1803 (information and infrastructure standards are not yet known.  At a minimum it is recognized) 1803 SB
246 881 1871 (that the global standards must not impair or restrict the creativity of equipment manufacturers,) 1871 SB
246 940 1864 (information providers or service providers, and must provide a realistic and stable base for the) 1864 SB
246 999 503 (envisioned infrastructure.) 503 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Italic /font31 ANSIFont font
359 1058 370 (Definition of GII: ) 370 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
729 1058 1386 (The Global Information Infrastructure \(GII\) is an infrastructure which) 1386 SB
246 1117 1676 (supports the development, implementation and interoperability of existing and future) 1676 SB
246 1176 1828 (information services and applications within and across the telecommunications, information) 1828 SB
246 1235 1714 (technology, consumer electronics and content provision industries.  This infrastructure) 1714 SB
246 1294 1772 (consists of interactive, broadcast and other multimedia delivery mechanisms coupled with) 1772 SB
246 1353 1710 (capabilities for individuals to securely share, use and manage information, anytime and) 1710 SB
246 1412 1560 (anywhere, at acceptable cost, quality, levels of security and privacy protection.) 1560 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Italic /font31 ANSIFont font
359 1471 227 (Why care? ) 227 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
586 1471 1493 ( GII will continue to develop regardless of what JTC1 does or does not do.) 1493 SB
246 1530 1854 (JTC1 investment in GII standards development and integration provides JTC1 greater market) 1854 SB
246 1589 1820 (relevancy.  GII standards are needed to achieve application and people interoperability, cost) 1820 SB
246 1648 1816 (effectiveness, and a high quality of service.  Global specifications are necessary for a timely,) 1816 SB
246 1707 1741 (successful GII.  Common services should be made available which can serve as reusable) 1741 SB
246 1766 1858 (building blocks for end user applications.  JTC1\222s Special Working Group on GII \(SWG-GII\)) 1858 SB
246 1825 1862 (recognizes the overarching impact the GII will have on existing SCs.  While not all existing or) 1862 SB
246 1884 1802 (future programs of work in JTC1 should be assumed to be part of the GII, few SCs, if any,) 1802 SB
246 1943 1564 (will not be contributing standards for the successful implementation of the GII.) 1564 SB
