246 245 272 (GII Services) 272 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
246 304 1835 (Standards that are potentialfundamental building blocks for GII Services should be identified) 1835 SB
246 363 1810 (using the form shown in Figure 2. The SC completing the form shall be clearly identified by) 1810 SB
246 422 1852 (replacing the two dots at the end of the form title with the SC number. The SC shall attach to) 1852 SB
246 481 1796 (the form a listing, of the type provided for the ISO catalogue and JTC1 status reports, that) 1796 SB
246 540 1836 (clearly associates the full title of each referenced standard with the number used to identify it) 1836 SB
246 599 231 (in the form.) 231 SB
246 717 1661 (When completing the form only the number of the relevant standard, draft standard,) 1661 SB
246 776 1808 (committee or working draft needs to be noted within the form. As an aid to comprehension) 1808 SB
246 835 1867 (this can be qualified \(in brackets\) by the acronym by which the standard is commonly referred,) 1867 SB
246 894 916 (e.g. IS 10918 \(JPEG\) or DIS 10743 \(SMDL\).) 916 SB
246 1012 1815 (Standards that support more than one fundamental building block, or which are relevant for) 1815 SB
246 1071 1717 (more than one service, should be listed in each relevant box. Where different parts of a) 1717 SB
246 1130 1736 (standard support different FBBs or services a part number should be specified using the) 1736 SB
246 1189 790 (standard ISO notation, e.g. IS 13818-3.) 790 SB
246 1307 1876 (When identifying where standards should be referenced care should be taken to ensure that the) 1876 SB
246 1366 1859 (standard conforms with the definitions of both the relevant FBB row and the relevant services) 1859 SB
246 1425 1788 (column given in this document. Where doubt as to the categorization exists an asterisk \(*\)) 1788 SB
246 1484 1322 (should be entered immediately after the standard number/acronym.) 1322 SB
246 1602 1766 (Where it is clear that a standard provides FBB\(s\) that conform to one or more of the sets) 1766 SB
246 1661 1735 (identified in the list, but for a service that could not, at even a stretch of imagination, be) 1735 SB
246 1720 1780 (assigned to one of the listed service categories, SCs may use the last column, or add extra) 1780 SB
246 1779 1846 (columns to the form, providing they formally define the scope of the service in terms that can) 1846 SB
246 1838 463 (be added to this report.) 463 SB
246 1956 1725 (Where SCs feel that a separate, generalized, category of fundamental building blocks is) 1725 SB
246 2015 1804 (required to clearly identify what their standards could offer to the GII community, they can) 1804 SB
246 2074 1770 (recommend an extension to the list of FBB categories at the next SWG-GII meeting. It is) 1770 SB
246 2133 1691 (recommended, however, that SCs wishing to do this ensure that their point of view is) 1691 SB
246 2192 1826 (adequately represented at the meeting to ensure that the SWG-GII does not misinterpret the) 1826 SB
246 2251 624 (impact of the proposed change.) 624 SB
