246 295 633 (GII Communication Services) 633 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
246 354 1735 (Standards that can use information provided by the fundamental building blocks for GII) 1735 SB
246 413 1714 (Services to implement communication networks that are appropriate for GII should be) 1714 SB
246 472 1750 (identified using the form shown in Figure 3. The SC completing the form shall be clearly) 1750 SB
246 531 1820 (identified by replacing the two dots at the end of the form title with the SC number. The SC) 1820 SB
246 590 1829 (shall attach to the form a listing, of the type provided for the ISO catalogue and JTC1 status) 1829 SB
246 649 1837 (reports, that clearly associates the full title of each referenced standard with the number used) 1837 SB
246 708 486 (to identify it in the form.) 486 SB
246 826 1661 (When completing the form only the number of the relevant standard, draft standard,) 1661 SB
246 885 1808 (committee or working draft needs to be noted within the form. As an aid to comprehension) 1808 SB
246 944 1867 (this can be qualified \(in brackets\) by the acronym by which the standard is commonly referred,) 1867 SB
246 1003 941 (e.g. IS 10021 \(MHS\) or  ISP 12063 \(EDIMG\).) 941 SB
246 1121 1815 (Standards that support more than one fundamental building block, or which are relevant for) 1815 SB
246 1180 1717 (more than one service, should be listed in each relevant box. Where different parts of a) 1717 SB
246 1239 1736 (standard support different FBBs or services a part number should be specified using the) 1736 SB
246 1298 790 (standard ISO notation, e.g. IS 10021-7.) 790 SB
246 1416 1815 (When identifying where standards should be referenced, care should be taken to ensure that) 1815 SB
246 1475 1763 (the standard conforms with the definitions of both the relevant FBB row and the relevant) 1763 SB
246 1534 1860 (services column. Where doubt as to the categorization exists an asterisk \(*\) should be entered) 1860 SB
246 1593 959 (immediately after the standard number/acronym.) 959 SB
246 1711 1766 (Where it is clear that a standard provides FBB\(s\) that conform to one or more of the sets) 1766 SB
246 1770 1735 (identified in the list, but for a service that could not, at even a stretch of imagination, be) 1735 SB
246 1829 1780 (assigned to one of the listed service categories, SCs may use the last column, or add extra) 1780 SB
246 1888 1846 (columns to the form, providing they formally define the scope of the service in terms that can) 1846 SB
246 1947 463 (be added to this report.) 463 SB
246 2065 1778 (The FBB categories currently listed in Figure 3 are those developed for GII Services. It is) 1778 SB
246 2124 1779 (expected that a detailed analysis of communications services will determine that certain of) 1779 SB
246 2183 1807 (these categories are invalid within a communications environment, and that other classes of) 1807 SB
246 2242 1798 (FBBs will be identified as being specific to this group of services. Where an SC feels that a) 1798 SB
246 2301 1816 (separate, generalized, category of fundamental building blocks is required to clearly identify) 1816 SB
246 2360 1814 (what their standards could offer to the GII community they can recommend an extension to) 1814 SB
246 2419 1802 (the list of FBB categories at the next SWG-GII meeting. It is recommended, however, that) 1802 SB
246 2478 1863 (SCs wishing to do this ensure that their point of view is adequately represented at the meeting) 1863 SB
246 2537 1700 (to ensure that the SWG-GII does not misinterpret the impact of the proposed change.) 1700 SB
1 #C
