321 295 1178 (Data Structures for Transport of Information Services) 1178 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
321 354 1652 (Standards that can use information provided by the fundamental building blocks for) 1652 SB
321 413 1649 (GII Services to provide data transport facilities when GII communication networks) 1649 SB
321 472 1700 (that are not appropriate can, if deemed relevant, be identified using the form shown in) 1700 SB
321 531 1677 (Figure 4. The SC completing the form shall be clearly identified by replacing the two) 1677 SB
321 590 1711 (dots at the end of the form title with the SC number. The SC shall attach to the form a) 1711 SB
321 649 1722 (listing, of the type provided for the ISO catalogue and JTC1 status reports, that clearly) 1722 SB
321 708 1693 (associates the full title of each referenced standard with the number used to identify it) 1693 SB
321 767 231 (in the form.) 231 SB
321 885 1661 (When completing the form only the number of the relevant standard, draft standard,) 1661 SB
321 944 1495 (committee or working draft needs to be noted within the form. As an aid to) 1495 SB
321 1003 1551 (comprehension this can be qualified \(in brackets\) by the acronym by which the) 1551 SB
321 1062 1439 (standard is commonly referred, e.g. IS 10175 \(DPA\) or IS 9069 \(SDIF\).) 1439 SB
321 1180 1573 (Standards that support more than one fundamental building block, or which are) 1573 SB
321 1239 1579 (relevant for more than one service, should be listed in each relevant box. Where) 1579 SB
321 1298 1678 (different parts of a standard support different FBBs or services a part number should) 1678 SB
321 1357 1203 (be specified using the standard ISO notation, e.g. IS 8613-5.) 1203 SB
321 1475 1713 (When identifying where standards should be referenced care should be taken to ensure) 1713 SB
321 1534 1681 (that the standard conforms with the definitions of both the relevant FBB row and the) 1681 SB
321 1593 1668 (relevant services column. Where doubt as to the categorization exists an asterisk \(*\)) 1668 SB
321 1652 1322 (should be entered immediately after the standard number/acronym.) 1322 SB
321 1770 1678 (Where it is clear that a standard provides FBB\(s\) that conform to one or more of the) 1678 SB
321 1829 1507 (sets identified in the list, but for a service that could not, at even a stretch of) 1507 SB
321 1888 1670 (imagination, be assigned to one of the listed service categories, SCs may use the last) 1670 SB
321 1947 1705 (column, or add extra columns to the form, providing they formally define the scope of) 1705 SB
321 2006 1030 (the service in terms that can be added to this report.) 1030 SB
321 2124 1689 (The FBB categories currently listed in Figure 4 are those developed for GII Services.) 1689 SB
321 2183 1675 (It is expected that a detailed analysis of physical data transfer services will determine) 1675 SB
321 2242 1646 (that certain of these categories are invalid within such environments, and that other) 1646 SB
321 2301 1699 (classes of FBBs will be identified as being specific to this group of services. Where an) 1699 SB
321 2360 1581 (SC feels that a separate, generalized, category of fundamental building blocks is) 1581 SB
321 2419 1710 (required to clearly identify what their standards could offer to the GII community they) 1710 SB
321 2478 1579 (can recommend an extension to the list of FBB categories at the next SWG-GII) 1579 SB
321 2537 1643 (meeting. It is recommended, however, that SCs wishing to do this ensure that their) 1643 SB
321 2596 1639 (point of view is adequately represented at the meeting to ensure that the SWG-GII) 1639 SB
321 2655 1131 (does not misinterpret the impact of the proposed change.) 1131 SB
32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Italic /font31 ANSIFont font
321 2773 1646 (Note: It is not expected that many of the fields in this form will ever be completed.) 1646 SB
