32 0 0 50 50 0 0 0 45 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
321 354 1597 (Standards that can use to input information required by the fundamental building) 1597 SB
321 413 1598 (blocks for GII Services to invoke data transport facilities via GII communication) 1598 SB
321 472 1697 (networks can, if deemed relevant, be identified using the form shown in Figure 5. The) 1697 SB
321 531 1701 (SC completing the form shall be clearly identified by replacing the two dots at the end) 1701 SB
321 590 1678 (of the form title with the SC number. The SC shall attach to the form a listing, of the) 1678 SB
321 649 1660 (type provided for the ISO catalogue and JTC1 status reports, that clearly associates) 1660 SB
321 708 1726 (the full title of each referenced standard with the number used to identify it in the form.) 1726 SB
321 826 1661 (When completing the form only the number of the relevant standard, draft standard,) 1661 SB
321 885 1495 (committee or working draft needs to be noted within the form. As an aid to) 1495 SB
321 944 1551 (comprehension this can be qualified \(in brackets\) by the acronym by which the) 1551 SB
321 1003 1656 (standard is commonly referred, e.g. IS 9995 \(Keyboards\) or IS 14755 \(UCS input\).) 1656 SB
321 1121 1573 (Standards that support more than one fundamental building block, or which are) 1573 SB
321 1180 1579 (relevant for more than one service, should be listed in each relevant box. Where) 1579 SB
321 1239 1678 (different parts of a standard support different FBBs or services a part number should) 1678 SB
321 1298 1203 (be specified using the standard ISO notation, e.g. IS 9995-2.) 1203 SB
321 1416 1713 (When identifying where standards should be referenced care should be taken to ensure) 1713 SB
321 1475 1681 (that the standard conforms with the definitions of both the relevant FBB row and the) 1681 SB
321 1534 1668 (relevant services column. Where doubt as to the categorization exists an asterisk \(*\)) 1668 SB
321 1593 1322 (should be entered immediately after the standard number/acronym.) 1322 SB
321 1711 1678 (Where it is clear that a standard provides FBB\(s\) that conform to one or more of the) 1678 SB
321 1770 1507 (sets identified in the list, but for a service that could not, at even a stretch of) 1507 SB
321 1829 1670 (imagination, be assigned to one of the listed service categories, SCs may use the last) 1670 SB
321 1888 1619 (column, or add additional columns to the form, providing they formally define the) 1619 SB
321 1947 1211 (scope of the service in terms that can be added to this report.) 1211 SB
321 2065 1665 (The FBB categories currently listed in Figure 5 are those identified by SWG-GII for) 1665 SB
321 2124 1628 (GII Services. It is expected that a detailed analysis of user interaction services will) 1628 SB
321 2183 1664 (determine that certain of these categories are invalid, and that other classes of FBBs) 1664 SB
321 2242 1673 (will be identified as being specific to this group of services. Where an SC feels that a) 1673 SB
321 2301 1655 (separate, generalized, category of fundamental building blocks is required to clearly) 1655 SB
321 2360 1720 (identify what their standards could offer to the GII community they can recommend an) 1720 SB
321 2419 1466 (extension to the list of FBB categories at the next SWG-GII meeting. It is) 1466 SB
321 2478 1691 (recommended, however, that SCs wishing to do this ensure that their point of view is) 1691 SB
321 2537 1502 (adequately represented at the meeting to ensure that the SWG-GII does not) 1502 SB
321 2596 948 (misinterpret the impact of the proposed change.) 948 SB
